      "content": "Of course, irresponsible outlets absolutely peddle outright lies, but the constant focus on this diverts attention from the bigger issue of corporate bias. Truly consequential misinformation often comes not from wacky blogs, but from mainstream sources that cherry-pick data to fit a predetermined agenda. We shouldn't fight every poorly worded headline; we must challenge the institutional gatekeepers who profit from manufacturing divisive outrage anyway. The system is rigged, not just the fringe websites.",
